$interpreted: PAFF: NEKO...NEKO!

PAFF: What do we do...she's not responding at all...
Could it be, that she ran into some kind of danger...?
Nora: I feel it's a simple case of you not being loud enough.
PAFF: Is that so? Then...Then I'll raise my voice...
Nora: That's not necessary. I'm concerned that you'll lure those monsters here instead.
PAFF: But...NEKO is...
Nora: Don't be so nervous. Stay close to Miss Nolva and we'll look for her together.
Nora: ...Miss Nolva?
Nolva: Waverlyde? Waverlyde?
PAFF: M...Miss Nolva?
Nolva: ...Yes?
Nolva: Eh, where are we now? What were you guys talking about?
PAFF: ...Who's this Waverlyde you just mentioned...?
Nolva: He's my monster friend. He usually lives inside my body. When I fall asleep, he'll take over my body to protect me.

Nolva: However, just now, Waverlyde...didn't respond...
...It's the first time this ever happened...
PAFF: Does this count...as some sort of split-personality?

Nora: The correct scientific name is dissociative identity disorder. When the personality switches, parts of their memory go missing.
The patient will be unable to remember what they did.
Nora: Are these your symptoms, Miss Nolva?
Nolva: Although I don't quite understand what you just said... that is indeed the case.
PAFF: ...Missing...memory...

Nolva: It's alright. I've been seeing this Dr. Clovis.
The medicine he prescribed me is very effective, so there's no need to worry.
PAFF: I see...Miss Nolva, you are truly strong-willed.
Nora: I agree. Okay, it's about time we get going.
Nora: ...Miss Nolva, it seems that they've caught up to us.
Nolva: Oh, this is bad...
PAFF: Look out! They're going to attack...
PAFF: AHHH!!
